{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "New rules for manufacturers of medical device implants",
        "additional_details": "We also believe it should be a legal requirement that if the manufacturer goes out of business, all the Intellectual Property (IP) - both hardware and software -  for the device must be made public.\r\n \r\nWe believe no one, and no company, should be allowed to essentially charge rent for any implant that is placed inside a person's body, and people should not be left with a device that cannot be maintained if its manufacturer goes bankrupt.\r\n",
        "background": "We believe it should be made illegal for manufacturers of medical devices implanted into patients to regularly charge the patient for upgrades or maintenance. ",
